                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Sept. 23: EIH Ltd, the operator of the Oberoi luxury hotel chain, will raise up to Rs 1,300 crore through a rights issue. The company has received approval from its board for raising the funds. The board at todays meeting accorded consent to a rights issue of equity shares not exceeding Rs 1,300 crore, it said. The company board has formed a committee to finalise the ratio, issue price and all procedural modalities relating to the issue.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 23: The government today cleared 24 foreign direct investment proposals worth over Rs 2,700 crore, of which Singapore-based power company Asian Genco Pte Ltd and Housing Development and Infrastructure Ltds proposals were of the highest value.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 23: Soft drinks and snacks major PepsiCo is understood to be looking at investing $500 million in India in the next two years for sustaining its high growth.
                                                                                                                          
